      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They were really strong in system design and had great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. Can you draft something professional and kind so we don't burn a bridge?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hey there! Writing a rejection email for a senior dev in Austin is a tough task, but we can definitely handle it with the right approach. You know, it's a bit like navigating a crowded marketplace where every vendor is trying to sell their wares; sometimes you just have to pick the one that fits your specific cart, even if another vendor had a really shiny display.\n\nHere is a draft that keeps things professional and kind, while keeping the door open for future collaborations.\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nHi [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview for the Senior Developer position here in Austin. We were genuinely impressed by your system design skills and your strong alignment with our culture. It was a pleasure getting to know you.\n\nWhile your background is impressive, we have decided to move forward with a candidate who has slightly more direct experience with our specific cloud stack. We know this is a tough decision, especially given how well you fit the picture.\n\nWe truly value the time you spent with us and would love to keep you in mind for future opportunities where your specific skillset might be a better match. We hope you understand our decision and wish you the",
